node.text:
Thank you once again to the @fargoairsho! From it being our commanding officer Cmdr. Brian Kesselring’s hometown, to debuting our commemorative gold flight suits, it was a memorable weekend for the entire team. We can’t wait to see you again! 

Next up: Eielson Air Force Base for the Arctic Lightning Air Show!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.text:
Good Morning Fargo! We’re here in North Dakota for the @fargoairsho and this is a very special weekend for us! This is the hometown of our very own Cmdr. Brian Kesselring, commanding officer and flight leader of the Blue Angels! Cmdr. Kesselring graduated from Fargo South High School in 1995, and then went on to graduate from Concordia College in 2000. The entire team is honored to represent the Navy and Marine Corps in Cmdr. Kesselring’s hometown. Come out and see us this weekend July 24-25th at the Hector International Airport!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.title: Cmdr. Kesselring flies over his hometown!

node.text:
Good Afternoon #BlueAngels fans! This past weekend was an incredible experience for our team. Being able to perform once again for the people of Pensacola Beach was amazing. Even with the rain, the best fans in the world came out to support! Thank you Pensacola Beach! Next stop, Fargo, North Dakota for the Fargo AirSho, July 24-25!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation

node.text:
Good Morning #BlueAngels fans! We’re excited to be in Buffalo, New York for the Thunder on the Buffalo Waterfront air show! We will be performing this Saturday and Sunday, June 19-20 at 3PM! Check out this video of our #5 Pilot, CDR Ben Walborn, as he practices over the Buffalo Waterfront!

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation #thunderonthebuffalowaterfront

node.title: CDR Ben Walborn Practice Flight over Buffalo Waterfront

node.text:
Day 1 of @dekeslaytonairfest is in the books! The weather was perfect for flying today and we had an amazing time! 

Check out this cockpit video from our #4 Pilot, Lt. Cmdr. Jim Cox @navyblueangel4 as the Diamond takes off during our Friday practice over La Crosse Regional Airport!

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation

node.text:
Congratulations to the #USNAClassof2021!

"You now know that you have what it takes to get through pretty much anything," said @vp Kamala Harris during the commencement address at the 
@USNavalAcademy. "So when you come up against an obstacle, when you experience a setback - and you will, we all do - remember the resilience that you showed this past year."

We look forward to seeing you in the fleet, Sailors and Marines!

#usnavy
#usmc
#blueangels

node.text:
“Representing my family, home town and the world famous Checkerboards of VMFA-312 is what makes me proud to be a Blue Angel!” - Sgt Dylan Lippard, Statesville, NC

The Airframes work center is responsible for maintaining flight controls; hydraulic systems; landing, arresting and catapult gear; and performs composite and sheet metal structural repairs on the F/A-18 Hornet.

Additional photos are from Lippard’s time at VMFA 312 and aboard the aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN 71). #OORAH to our Marine Corps teammates! 

#MaintainerMonday @usnavy @marines #USMC

node.text:
Thank you once again to the @fargoairsho! From it being our commanding officer Cmdr. Brian Kesselring’s hometown, to debuting our commemorative gold flight suits, it was a memorable weekend for the entire team. We can’t wait to see you again! 

Next up: Eielson Air Force Base for the Arctic Lightning Air Show!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.text:
Thanks for the amazing air show Fargo! Yesterday we debuted our yellow flight suits in celebration and commemoration of 75 years of Blue Angels history and heritage. The team regularly dons the uniform for milestone anniversary show seasons with the last time being the 70th Anniversary show season in 2016. It was an honor to perform for you this weekend at the @fargoairsho!

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.text:
"If I can inspire just one person to pursue greatness with the photos and videos I create, then I’ve done my job." - Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Cody Hendrix, Beaufort, SC.

The Public Affairs Office documents and promotes the Blue Angels. It designs, writes, photographs, edits, publishes and distributes news and promotional materials for the squadron. The Public Affairs Office also coordinates promotional coverage and interviews with local, national and international media, and manages the Blue Angels VIP rider program.

Photos from the fleet are from his time aboard USS Ronald Reagan (CVN 76) and AFN Europe. 

#MaintainerMonday #BlueAngels @usnavy @marines

node.text:
Good Morning Fargo! We’re here in North Dakota for the @fargoairsho and this is a very special weekend for us! This is the hometown of our very own Cmdr. Brian Kesselring, commanding officer and flight leader of the Blue Angels! Cmdr. Kesselring graduated from Fargo South High School in 1995, and then went on to graduate from Concordia College in 2000. The entire team is honored to represent the Navy and Marine Corps in Cmdr. Kesselring’s hometown. Come out and see us this weekend July 24-25th at the Hector International Airport!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

"On this team, we challenge ourselves to maintain a standard of excellence day in and day out. Not only do we strive to better ourselves personally and professionally, but through dedication, teamwork and professionalism, we impact one another and the community around us. That aspect is what I love most about this team and want to take back to the Fleet." LS1 Vince Smith, Jacksonville, NC.

Vince is a member of the logistics department. The Logistics Department researches, procures, stores, and dispatches spare parts, tools, and uniforms. Logistics personnel also research future squadron logistical needs, and initiate contracts for services required to support daily operations.

Photos from the fleet during his time with USS Iwo Jima LHD 7 and Joint Task Force Civil Support
